---
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />

    <title>Andrew Coco | Growth & Web Strategy Leader</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Andrew Coco is a growth and web strategy executive at Peacock and NBCUniversal leading AI discovery, SEO, acquisition systems, experimentation, and subscription growth." />
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://www.andrewco.co/" />

    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://www.andrewco.co/" />
    <meta property="og:title" content="Andrew Coco | SEO, GEO, Growth & Web Strategy Leader" />
    <meta property="og:description" content="Growth and web strategy executive at Peacock and NBCUniversal. AI discovery, SEO, acquisition systems, experimentation, and subscription growth." />
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://www.andrewco.co/andrew_coco.png" />
    <meta property="og:image:alt" content="Andrew Coco, Senior Director of Web Strategy at Peacock and NBCUniversal" />
    <meta property="og:site_name" content="Andrew Coco" />

    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
    <meta name="twitter:title" content="Andrew Coco | Growth & Web Strategy Leader" />
    <meta name="twitter:description" content="Growth and web strategy executive at Peacock and NBCUniversal. AI discovery, SEO, acquisition systems, experimentation, and subscription growth." />
    <meta name="twitter:image" content="https://www.andrewco.co/andrew_coco.png" />

    <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Person",
      "name": "Andrew Coco",
      "url": "https://www.andrewco.co",
      "image": "https://www.andrewco.co/andrew_coco.png",
      "jobTitle": "Senior Director of Web Strategy, SEO & AI Search",
      "worksFor": {
        "@type": "Organization",
        "name": "Peacock / NBCUniversal"
      },
      "alumniOf": {
        "@type": "EducationalOrganization",
        "name": "San Diego State University"
      },
      "award": "Sports Emmy Award, 46th Sports Emmys 2025",
      "sameAs": [
        "https://www.linkedin.com/in/andrewcoco/"
      ],
      "knowsAbout": [
        "Web Strategy",
        "SEO",
        "AI Discovery Strategy",
        "Generative Engine Optimization",
        "Acquisition Systems",
        "Conversion Rate Optimization",
        "Experimentation",
        "Subscription Growth",
        "Media Digital Strategy",
        "Growth Leadership"
      ]
    }
    </script>
  </head>

  <body>

    <header class="site-header">
      <div class="container header-inner">
        <a href="/" class="wordmark">Andrew Coco</a>
        <nav aria-label="Primary navigation">
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/andrewcoco/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main id="main-content">

      <!-- HERO -->
      <section class="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-heading">
        <div class="container hero-inner">

          <div class="hero-text">
            <p class="hero-eyebrow">Web Strategy · AI Discovery · Subscription Growth</p>
            <h1 id="hero-heading">Andrew Coco</h1>
            <p class="hero-tagline">Building acquisition systems for the AI era of discovery.</p>
            <p class="hero-sub">I lead web strategy, SEO, AI discovery, experimentation, and conversion programs that drive audience and subscription growth at scale.</p>

            <div class="hero-credentials">
              <div class="hero-credential">
                <span class="credential-label">Now</span>
                <span class="credential-value">Sr. Director, Web Strategy, SEO & AI Search · Peacock / NBCUniversal</span>
              </div>
              <div class="hero-credential">
                <span class="credential-label">Previously</span>
                <span class="credential-value">The Walt Disney Company · GUESS? · Digitas</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="hero-photo">
            <img
              src="/andrew_coco.png"
              alt="Andrew Coco, Senior Director of Web Strategy at Peacock and NBCUniversal"
              width="280"
              height="280"
              loading="eager"
              fetchpriority="high"
            />
            <span class="hero-photo-name">Andrew Coco</span>
            <span class="hero-photo-eyebrow">Web Strategy · AI Discovery · Subscription Growth</span>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ABOUT -->
      <section class="section about" aria-labelledby="about-heading">
        <div class="container">
          <h2 id="about-heading" class="section-label">About</h2>
          <div class="about-body">
            <p>I lead growth and web strategy initiatives focused on acquisition, discovery, and conversion across large-scale consumer platforms.</p>
            <p>At NBCUniversal, my scope spans two distinct business lines. For Peacock, I oversee web strategy, SEO, generative engine optimization, app store optimization, conversion rate optimization, and AI discovery — building the acquisition and owned web systems that drive direct subscription growth. Across NBC.com, NBC Sports, and NBC Olympics, I lead SEO strategy and organic search programs that serve some of the most trafficked media properties in the country.</p>
            <p>SEO remains the foundation of everything I do. It is also the lens through which I approach AI discovery — because the signals, content systems, and authority structures that drive traditional search performance are increasingly the same ones that determine visibility in generative and AI-powered interfaces. I also chair a cross-organization AI search committee at NBCUniversal focused on growing visibility across emerging discovery surfaces.</p>
            <p>My background spans media, subscription, e-commerce, and digital growth organizations, with experience leading cross-functional initiatives across Product, Engineering, Editorial, Analytics, Marketing, and Growth teams.</p>
            <p>I think of myself as a strategist who understands search deeply, not the other way around.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- FOCUS AREAS -->
      <section class="section focus" aria-labelledby="focus-heading">
        <div class="container">
          <h2 id="focus-heading" class="section-label">Focus Areas</h2>
          <ul class="focus-grid" role="list">
            <li class="focus-item">
              <h3>AI Discovery & Search Strategy</h3>
              <p>Helping organizations adapt to AI-driven discovery ecosystems, evolving search behavior, and changing consumer acquisition patterns across generative and traditional search surfaces.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="focus-item">
              <h3>Growth & Acquisition Systems</h3>
              <p>Building scalable acquisition systems across owned web, organic discovery, experimentation, and conversion optimization that compound over time.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="focus-item">
              <h3>Experimentation & Conversion</h3>
              <p>Developing testing cultures and optimization frameworks that improve acquisition efficiency and customer journey performance at every stage of the funnel.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="focus-item">
              <h3>Web Product & Platform Strategy</h3>
              <p>Treating owned web as a strategic growth surface. Architecture, experience, and strategy aligned to business outcomes rather than channel metrics.</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- WHAT I'M THINKING ABOUT -->
      <section class="section thinking" aria-labelledby="thinking-heading">
        <div class="container">
          <h2 id="thinking-heading" class="section-label">What I'm Thinking About</h2>
          <ul class="thinking-list" role="list">
            <li>
              <strong>AI discovery is reshaping audience acquisition faster than most organizations are prepared for.</strong>
              <p>Traditional search assumptions are breaking down as AI assistants and generative interfaces become primary discovery layers. Most companies are still operating with measurement systems built for an earlier internet.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Owned web strategy matters more, not less.</strong>
              <p>As platforms increasingly intermediate attention, owned experiences become more important as conversion, retention, and brand surfaces. The role of the website is evolving from destination to growth infrastructure.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>The future growth leaders will combine product, acquisition, and AI strategy.</strong>
              <p>The historical separation between search, product growth, web strategy, and experimentation is collapsing. The organizations that adapt fastest will build integrated growth systems rather than channel silos.</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- LEADERSHIP -->
      <section class="section leadership" aria-labelledby="leadership-heading">
        <div class="container">
          <h2 id="leadership-heading" class="section-label">Leadership</h2>
          <div class="leadership-body">
            <p>I believe the next generation of growth organizations will be defined by cross-functional thinking, experimentation cultures, and adaptability to platform change.</p>
            <p>The strongest teams I've built and been part of combine strategic clarity with technical depth, operational rigor with product thinking, and a genuine curiosity about how consumer behavior is shifting. Titles and channel ownership matter less than the ability to connect strategy to outcome across functions.</p>
            <p>I'm particularly interested in building organizations that can move quickly when ecosystems shift, and that treat AI, search, and digital distribution as strategic questions rather than tactical ones.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- BACKGROUND -->
      <section class="section background" aria-labelledby="background-heading">
        <div class="container">
          <h2 id="background-heading" class="section-label">Background</h2>

          <div class="background-body">

            <div class="bg-block">
              <h3 class="bg-block-title">Experience</h3>
              <ol class="career-list" role="list">

                <li class="career-item career-item--group">
                  <div class="career-group-header">
                    <span class="career-date">2021 — Present</span>
                  </div>
                  <ol class="career-subroles" role="list">
                    <li class="career-subitem">
                      <div class="career-meta">
                        <span class="career-role">Sr. Director, Web Strategy, SEO & AI Search</span>
                        <span class="career-company">NBCUniversal</span>
                         <span class="career-company">Peacock · NBC.com · NBC Sports · NBC Olympics</span>
                      </div>
                      <span class="career-date">2025 — Present</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="career-subitem">
                      <div class="career-meta">
                        <span class="career-role">Director, SEO</span>
                        <span class="career-company">NBCUniversal</span>
                          <span class="career-company">Peacock · NBC Sports · NBC Olympics</span>
                      </div>
                      <span class="career-date">2021 — 2025</span>
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                </li>

                <li class="career-item">
                  <div class="career-meta">
                    <span class="career-role">Sr. SEO Manager, Customer Engagement</span>
                    <span class="career-company">The Walt Disney Company</span>
                     <span class="career-company">DisneyStore.com · Disney Stores</span>
                  </div>
                  <span class="career-date">2020 — 2021</span>
                </li>
                <li class="career-item">
                  <div class="career-meta">
                    <span class="career-role">E-Commerce SEO Manager</span>
                    <span class="career-company">GUESS?</span>
                    <span class="career-company">GUESS? USA · GUESS? Canada</span>
                  </div>
                  <span class="career-date">2018 — 2020</span>
                </li>
                <li class="career-item">
                  <div class="career-meta">
                    <span class="career-role">Sr. SEO Specialist</span>
                    <span class="career-company">HZDG (acquired by Burson, WPP)</span>
                  </div>
                  <span class="career-date">2017 — 2018</span>
                </li>
                <li class="career-item">
                  <div class="career-meta">
                    <span class="career-role">Search Marketing Analyst</span>
                    <span class="career-company">Digitas</span>
                    <span class="career-company">Supported: Taco Bell · Matel · STARZ</span>
                  </div>
                  <span class="career-date">2016 — 2017</span>
                </li>
                <li class="career-item">
                  <div class="career-meta">
                    <span class="career-role">SEO Coordinator</span>
                    <span class="career-company">Geary LSF</span>
                  </div>
                  <span class="career-date">2015 — 2016</span>
                </li>
              </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-block">
              <h3 class="bg-block-title">Education</h3>
              <ol class="career-list" role="list">
                <li class="career-item">
                  <div class="career-meta">
                    <span class="career-role">B.S. Business Administration, Marketing</span>
                    <span class="career-company">San Diego State University</span>
                  </div>
                </li>
              </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-block">
              <h3 class="bg-block-title">Selected Highlights</h3>
              <div class="highlights-grid">

                <div class="highlight-group">
                  <h4 class="highlight-group-title">Awards</h4>
                  <ul class="highlight-list">
                    <li>Sports Emmy Award — Outstanding Interactive Experience, 2024 Paris Olympics (NBC / Peacock)</li>
                    <li>Named one of the 53 Best SEO Experts of 2020, Northstar Inbound</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="highlight-group">
                  <h4 class="highlight-group-title">Speaking</h4>
                  <ul class="highlight-list">
                    <li>Organizer & speaker, NBCUniversal Internal SEO Summit — 200+ attendees, 25 speakers</li>
                    <li>Speaker, SEO Day — presented across two events to a combined 179K attendees</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="highlight-group">
                  <h4 class="highlight-group-title">Press & Publishing</h4>
                  <ul class="highlight-list">
                    <li>Quoted Contributor, Search Engine Journal</li>
                    <li>Featured contributor, Rankz.IO · JBH.co.uk · SEO for Journalism</li>
                    <li>Roundtable contributor, SEMrush — 5 Hours of Technical SEO</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>

              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- CONTACT -->
      <section class="section contact" aria-labelledby="contact-heading">
        <div class="container">
          <h2 id="contact-heading" class="section-label">Get in Touch</h2>
          <p class="contact-intro">Open to conversations about web strategy, AI discovery, media growth, and the future of owned web.</p>
          <div class="contact-links">
            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/andrewcoco/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="contact-btn">Connect on LinkedIn</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

    </main>

    <footer class="site-footer">
      <div class="container footer-inner">
        <p class="footer-name">Andrew Coco</p>
        <p class="footer-copy">&copy; 2025 · andrewco.co</p>
      </div>
    </footer>

  </body>
</html>